From: Codex <codex@openai.com>
Date: Mon, 20 Jul 2026 07:12:00 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] p2: pin posix constdef comparator

posix module initialization sorts its exported configuration-name tables with
qsort.  The comparator callback currently occupies a standalone overlay, so
each qsort callback can reload code for a two-field strcmp.

The exact r12 linked layout records a 0x30-byte cmp_constdefs overlay body and
a 0x4-byte resident entry stub.  That image has 436 bytes of raw staging
headroom.  Moving the 48-byte body resident and removing the four-byte stub
therefore adds exactly 44 bytes and leaves 392 bytes.  Mark only this callback
resident; the placement macro is empty away from NuttX P2, preserving generic
CPython code generation and behavior.
---
 Modules/posixmodule.c | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/Modules/posixmodule.c b/Modules/posixmodule.c
--- a/Modules/posixmodule.c
+++ b/Modules/posixmodule.c
@@ -14546,6 +14546,7 @@ os_sysconf_impl(PyObject *module, int name)
  * easier to add additional entries to the tables.
  */
 
+_Py_P2_HUB_RESIDENT
 static int
 cmp_constdefs(const void *v1,  const void *v2)
 {
-- 
2.50.1
